status: MARC21-007: Literary text of sound recordings
Indicate the type of literary text contained in a nonmusical sound recording.

preferred label (en): item is a musical sound recording
definition (en): Item is a musical sound recording

scope note (en): Includes instructions on how to accomplish a task, learn an art, etc. (e.g., how to replace a light switch). Not used for language instruction.

definition (en): Not a sound recording (e.g., printed or manuscript music).
Performances of any of a variety of nonmusical productions.

Literary text for sound recordings other than autobiography, biography, conference proceedings, drama, essays, fiction, reporting, history, instruction, language instruction, comedy, lectures, speeches, memoirs, folktales, poetry, rehearsals, sounds, interviews.
